The paper deals with the problem of robots ferrying messages between source and sink pairs in a wireless network, which involves coordination and control of multiple agents. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Multiagent Systems (cs.MA) category. Additionally, the paper deals with wireless communication and network optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. The use of robots for message ferrying suggests that the paper could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category. The paper also involves analysis and optimization of network capacity, which suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. Finally, the paper involves the use of control policies to stabilize the network, which suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
